article.description: Anderson leads Robert Morris by Sacred Heart 79-70
article.headline: Anderson leads Robert Morris by Sacred Heart 79-70
article.linkText: Anderson leads Robert Morris by Sacred Heart 79-70
article.story: FAIRFIELD, Conn. -- Karvel Anderson scored a career-high 36 points and Robert Morris defeated Sacred Heart 79-70 in the Northeast Conference opener for both teams on Thursday night. Sacred Heart (3-13, 0-1) trailed by nine points at halftime before coming within 72-70 after De'von Barnett made 1 of 2 free throws with 2 minutes remaining. Anderson then scored the next five points, including a 3-pointer with 29 seconds remaining, to put Robert Morris up 77-70. Robert Morris (6-10, 1-0) shot 53.6 percent from the field, including 10 of 15 from long range. Anderson hit 6 of his 7 3-point attempts. Lucky Jones added 17 points for the Colonials. Robert Morris, playing its fourth of five consecutive road contests, snapped a three-game losing streak which included losses to Alabama and No. 6 Oklahoma State. Mostafa Abdel Latif led Sacred Heart with 17 points and 12 rebounds.
